ASUS has announced new ZenBook and VivoBook laptop models, all of which will feature ScreenPad 2.0. ScreenPad 2.0 is an upgrade of the track pad technology ASUS introduced with last year’s ZenBook Pro. This solution integrates a 5.65-inch secondary screen into the laptop’s track pad, allowing you to perform functions like controlling your media player or activating keyboard macros. It also lets you swipe between multiple screens of shortcuts and long-press on icons to move or delete them. Where previously the ScreenPad used the power-hungry discrete graphics processor of the laptop, it now uses the CPU’s integrated Intel graphics, offering over twice the battery life. The new ASUS ZenBook 14 and 15 will be available in South Africa from August, beginning at R26,999. ASUS VivoBook S14 and S15 will also be available from August, starting at R16,999. There will also be VivoBook models available without ScreenPad 2.0. Specifications for each of these new laptops are summarised below. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-307690" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/ASUS-ZenBook-top.jpg" alt="ASUS ZenBook top" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/ASUS-ZenBook-top.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/ASUS-ZenBook-top-300x202.jpg 300w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/ASUS-ZenBook-top-595x400.jpg 595w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" />  <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-307686" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/ASUS-ZenBook-2019-angle-left.jpg" alt="ASUS ZenBook 2019 angle left" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/ASUS-ZenBook-2019-angle-left.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/ASUS-ZenBook-2019-angle-left-300x202.jpg 300w, https